1. Installing from tarball distribution

- Untar @PACKAGE@ tarball
$ tar xzvf @PACKAGE@-@VERSION@.tar.gz
- Change dir to @PACKAGE@-@VERSION@
$ cd @PACKAGE@-@VERSION@
- run configure script
$ ./configure
- run make
$ make
- to install switch to root
$ su -c 'make install'

2. Building rpm package from tarball distribution

- build binary package
$ rpm -tb @PACKAGE@-@VERSION@.tar.gz
- install binary package
$ su -c "rpm -Uhv /path_to_RPMS_dir/@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@-1.i386.rpm"

